06/08/2009
ANKARA, Turkey -- Russian Prime Minister Vladimir Putin is in Ankara on Thursday (August 6th), for talks with Turkish counterpart Recep Tayyip Erdogan. 
The focus will be energy projects, including Russia's South Stream gas pipeline, which would pass under Turkey's territorial waters. 
The two leaders are also expected to sign a nuclear energy deal, in which Russia would help Turkey build nuclear power plants. 
(BBC - 06/08/09; Beta, B92, RTS, AFP - 05/08/09)
